data.title: Real Housewives of Atlanta: Ralph Pittman leaves Drew Sidora CRYING
data.meta_description: Ralph Pittman stormed off and left Drew Sidora crying at an elaborate candlelight romantic dinner after she wanted to talk to him about their relationship on Sunday night's The Real Housewives of Atlanta.
data.text:
Ralph Pittman stormed off and left Drew Sidora crying at an elaborate candlelight romantic dinner after she wanted to talk to him about their relationship on Sunday night's The Real Housewives of Atlanta.

Ralph, 38, had gone to great lengths to plan the dinner that he hoped would show Drew how much he cared for her. He flew in her glam squad to get her ready and laid out a red carpet to a chauffeured car that whisked her away from their house to a surprise location.

'Where am I?' Drew, 37, said to Ralph after she got there.

'This is my tailor's showroom, actually,' Ralph said.

Ralph then led her out to a candlelit table with a giant red roses centerpiece surrounded on the floor by multiple red rose floral arrangements.

'I want to make sure that my wife knows that no woman can ever come close to her,' Ralph said in a confessional.

'Sometimes I can be an a**hole,' Ralph said. 'But the thing about it is, you know I love you. I want to be the best husband, the best father, the best provider.'

'This is what I live for you,' Drew said. 'Because you do go out of my way to make me feel like the most important thing in the world. I just want to make sure that we don't have these really high highs, and we go through those lows. And really deal with our problems on a deeper level so we can be healthy for each other.'

'I agree,' Ralph said.

Ralph said he wanted them to just enjoy the night and to save everything else for marriage counseling.

'This shows me we can make it,' Drew said.

'This shows you?' Ralph said. 'You know I am going to schedule a session for you to go and speak to Dr. Ken on how to speak to men appropriately to get whatever you're trying to do across effectively.'

'Yes, and I will pay for you to have a session to learn how to talk to women,' Drew said.

Ralph said that Dr. Ken said that Drew used zingers. Drew said that Dr. Ken called him a maniac.

'Nobody that's a maniac is this successful,' Ralph said. 'For you to go and repeat what he says.'

'You have maniac tendencies,' Drew said.

When Ralph got upset, Drew apologized for saying anything.

'We both have work to do,' Drew said.

'How about you just try to have a good night,' Ralph said.

'Me expressing myself means we are having a bad night then what the hell are we doing,' Drew said as she started to cry.

'Really this is bullsh**,' Ralph said. 'Tonight was not the night to go and try to fix anything.'

'Let's just have a conversation, that's all I'm asking for,' Drew said.

'Doing stuff for you is not the move,' Ralph said as he walked off. 'I regret doing this,'

In the episode titled 'All Aboard the Gaslight Express,' opened with Sanya Richards-Ross, 36, explaining that she moved her family to be with her and her husband NFL alum Aaron Ross, 39, in Atlanta. She said she now had nine people living in the house including her parents and her sister Shari, her husband and her twin boys.

'The house is definitely crowded,' Sanya said in a confessional. 'My sister is actually my hairstylist. My Mom still manages me. Having them in Atlanta is going to give me everything I need to take the world by storm.'

Shere Whitfield, 51, invited Kenya Moore, 51, over to see her new 'Chateau.' Her mother Thelma asked her if Kenya ate sweets.

'I don't know, the b**** skinny as hell, right now,' Shere said. 'She may not be eating nothing.'

'Look at your chateau,' said Kenya when she came over.

Shere said she could not wait to show Kenya her finished basement with a spa area and high ceilings.

'I love it, Shere,' Kenya said when she saw it.

Shere told Kenya that she looked happy and she liked the way she was now.

'I almost love you, b****,' Shere said.

Kenya asked her what she thought about Marlo's 'gala.'

'The whole fake and pretentious, I got money,' Kenya said. It's just kind of, like, it's a turn off to me.'

Shere said that Marlo was also talking about her and about how she once lived in an apartment with a white refrigerator.

'What's wrong with a white refrigerator,' Kenya said. 'At least, I could pay my rent.'

Shere said that Marlo also said that she rented Lisa Ray McCoy's Range Rover. They called Sanya and asked her what she remembered from the party. Kenya said she had love for Marlo.

Kenya said that Kandi Burruss, 45, heard that one of Drew Sidora' assistant's called Anthony was also one of Shere's assistants.

'She said that you owe the assistant money,' Kenya said to Shere. 'And that he has been going back to Drew, telling all your personal business.'

'Shut your face,' Shere said.

Shere said she knew who she was talking about but that she hardly ever uses him. Kenya said there was just a lot of mess going on over there because Drew's husband got entangled with her other assistant that offered to give massages.

At Drew's house, Drew and Ralph sat down for a family dinner. Drew said she had fun at Marlo's event. Drew told him that she spoke to Kandi at the event and that she brought up the Instagram of Ralph's assistant.

'Look, I fired her,' Ralph said.

'Okay, so you don't talk anymore?' Drew asked.

'I didn't say we don't talk anymore I just said we're not doing business,' Ralph said.

'So you all do still talk?' Drew said.

'I said 'I am no longer going to work with her anymore,' Ralph said.

'He will confuse me and I'll be like 'am I tripping?' Drew said in a confessional.

Drew said to him that if he ever found something in her phone of a guy offering her a massage that he would have a problem with that.

'That's not what happened,' Ralph said.

'You are making me really feel like I'm crazy , like I'm not making sense, when I know I have a valid point,' Drew said.

In a confessional, Drew said that people say that Ralph gaslight's her but she didn't know if that was true. A producer asked her define gaslighting and she looked it up on her phone.

'Oh manipulates someone by psychological means into questioning their own sanity,' Drew said reading from her phone. 'Oh my God.'

Marlo took her 14-year-old nephew Michael shopping for a suit for homecoming. Kenya spent time at her house with her two-year-old daughter Brooklyn.

At her house, Kandi called Brian Moreland, her Broadway co-producer on the play 'Thoughts of A Colored Man.' They discussed the play's opening night and its reviews.

'An all black production to be able to get a show on Broadway that's never happened before,' Kandi said in a confessional. 'I mean, it was called the Great White Way. So, to be able to put a little color in it, is history in the making, and I'm just glad to be a part of it.'

Todd walked in and she told him she was 'on cloud nine.' Kandi told him that she was also feeling overwhelmed and that he had been taking multiple vacations.

'You leave for months,' Todd said.

'When I'm gone, I'm gone for work,' Kandi said. 'Why are you going to Miami?'

'To hang out,' Todd said.

Kandi and Todd then went to look at their pool room which was only half finished to try and make some decisions on what to do. Todd said he could take some of the furniture and put it in his condo in Jersey.

'He wants to share it with me but this was your spot with your ex,' Kandi said in a confessional of the Jersey condo. 'I don't really want to do that.'

'The house that she had when we met, she had already bumped and grinded all kinds of craziness in that house,' Todd said in a confessional. 'She didn't even flip the mattress over.'

Kandi told him that she thought he cared more about redoing his New Jersey apartment than fixing their house.

Marlo went to meet Kandi at a studio. Kandi was painted green and dressed like a witch in a black leather outfit.

'This is the perfect costume for me,' Kandi said.

Kandi told Marlo that she loved how she put together her fashion event and how she was such a great aunt to her nephew. Marlo told her that her nephews were stressing her out a little bit.

'I've just created little monsters,' Marlo said. 'I bought a $1,200 suit for homecoming.'

'Why does being Black have to equate to struggle,' Kandi said.

'People always feel like they have to come up from the gutter and that's not necessarily true,' Kandi said in a confessional. 'I think we can still instill a work ethic in our children and still have them set up for greatness.'

Marlo said she really thought it takes a village to raise children.

'You're the only one that's sending cash out for graduation or birthday,' Marlo said to Kandi. 'I appreciate that but I would also appreciate even more hands on.'

Marlo said Kandi had never invited her over for movie night.

'You have got to be the type of friend that you want,' Kandi said.

At Drew's house, Ralph told her after they worked out to keep her schedule clear because he wanted to do something just for them.

'We got to get back to us because if we are coming from a place where we don't like each other then anything can break us apart,' Ralph said.

'I get that,' Drew said.

Todd, Ralph and Aaron 'Ross' met up at to Kandi & Todd's restaurant. Todd told them that he had four kids. Aaron said he wanted another one but that Sanya wasn't sold on having another child. Todd told Ralph that he had a lot of conversations with his wife about his assistant.

'Oh really?' Ralph said. 'Here's the thing that wifey cannot let go of.'

'Here comes the bullsh**, '' Todd said.

'I cannot find a massage therapist,' Ralph said.

Todd laughed and winked at Ralph.

'It's hard to explain,' Ralph said in a confessional. 'It's a matter of you believing exactly what I sayBut really Drew should never have been going through my cell phone to begin with.'

Todd explained to them he was having problems with Kandi about his condo in New Jersey.

At Marlo's house, Michael talked about being nervous about having to dance at homecoming. Marlo gave him some quick dance lessons. Marlo then helped him get dressed.

'When I lived with my mother, I had it tough, '' Marlo said in a confessional. 'I grew up in the projects. My mom was on drugs. My Mama, that b**** getting high, and I got my a** beat all the time. Foster care was my safe haven.'

'I want Michael to sit back on his sad days and say 'wow, I remember my first homecoming,' ' Marlo said. 'I was living with my auntie and she went all the way out.'

Marlo hugged Michael and said she was so proud of him.

Real Housewives of Atlanta will return next Sunday on Bravo
